sql:
SELECT cell_name
FROM cells
ORDER BY cell_name ASC;

SELECT chembl_id
FROM molecules
ORDER BY chembl_id;

SELECT name, department
FROM researchers
WHERE researcher_id IN (
  SELECT researcher_id
  FROM collaborations
);

external_knowledge:
- High average pchembl_value typically corresponds to more potent compounds; 
- ChEMBL ID is a unique identifier for each molecule; 
- Experiments with more recent dates are considered more important for this context.

